                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Mountain <sic>Collage</sic>, Cote St Catharine</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                <date>15 August 1865</date>.</p>\n            <p>My dear Sir—</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Yours of <date>13th</date> ult. Found<lb/> me out of town—like\n                yourself, I have<lb/> been moving about a little-though<lb/> my circuit has not\n                extended to <placeName>Yankee-<lb/>land</placeName>. I was sorry to find you\n                had<lb/> been suffering somewhat from lungs<lb/> &amp; throat. Being myself\n                somewhat<lb/> delicate in those regions, and a<lb/> fellow feeling making us\n                wondrous<lb/> kind, I felt for you, and trust<lb/> that your trip south has\n                helped<lb/> completely to restore you. With reference<lb/> to your visit to\n                    <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>—had I been<lb/> in time I should have urged you\n                to<lb/> continue in office as President of<lb/> your district of Benai Berith, for\n                since<lb/> this <sic>organisation</sic>, which I view with<lb/> anything but favor,\n                has assumed its<lb/> present proportions, I suppose we<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">must</hi> look after it, lest our humble</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3db7w98g/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
