                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>modest pious &amp;c reform brethren use<lb/> it as a tool—a terrible one too—<lb/>\n                against orthodoxy. But I <hi rend=\"underline\">hate</hi> the<lb/> very idea of a\n                Jewish secret society—<lb/> no Roman Catholic prelate ever hated<lb/> masonry\n                orangeism Ribbonism or any<lb/> other secret ism more than I abhor<lb/> such an\n                organisation among us-<lb/> or one at all approaching these Christian<lb/> religious\n                or political secret societies.<lb/> But I am not going to trouble you<lb/> with a\n                disquisition on them, especially<lb/> as I have an abominable pen which<lb/> will\n                stick into the paper, and being<lb/> away from home I cannot change it.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I will, as usual, bring the<lb/> circular you enclosed me\n                prominently<lb/> before our small circle here—I fear<lb/> with but little success.\n                We have<lb/> too many Polish &amp; German brethren<lb/> for <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >English</hi>-books—though not<lb/> for synagogue purposes, and I don't<lb/>\n                know what I should do without<lb/> them. I sometimes think I am</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3db7w98g/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
